Ingredients:

1/2 cup milk
1/2 cup water
1 cup all-purpose flour
2 eggs
1/4 teaspoon salt
2 tablespoons butter, melted
1 tablespoon olive oil
3 cloves garlic, minced
3 cups fresh spinach
2 cups chicken breast, cooked and shredded
1 cup mozzarella cheese, shredded
Juice of a lemon
Salt and pepper
2 tablespoons butter
2 tablespoons flour
1 1/4 cups milk, warm
Salt
Freshly ground pepper
1/8 teaspoon nutmeg

Steps:

1. Preheat oven to 375 degrees.

2. In a blender, add milk, water, flour, eggs, salt and melted butter. Blend until smooth. Refrigerate for at least 30 minutes.

3. Lightly oil a frying pan with melted butter. Place over medium-high heat.

4. Pour in 1/4 cup batter, and tilt the pan with a circular motion until the batter coats the surface evenly.

5. Cook the crepe for about 2 minutes, until it bubbles up and loosens from the pan. Flip and cook for 2 more minutes on the other side.

6. In a heavy-bottomed pan on medium-high heat, add 1 tablespoon of olive oil.

7. Add garlic and cook until aromatic, about 2 minutes.

8. Add spinach, chicken and mozzarella and cook for 4 minutes.

9. Add lemon juice and season with salt and pepper.

10. Place crepe on a baking sheet or cast-iron pan, place 2 tablespoons of filling in the center and fold up. Repeat with remaining crepes.

11. Pour sauce over the crepes, and broil for 5 to 8 minutes until golden brown.

12. In a heavy-bottomed saucepan, melt butter.

13. Stir in the flour and cook, stirring constantly, until it cooks out, about 2 minutes.

14. Add the warm milk, salt, pepper, and nutmeg, continuing to stir as the sauce thickens.

15. Bring to a boil, then remove from heat.

It's everything you love about Camp Kikiwaka...on a cake! Duo Connor & Emerson dreamed up this "Bunk'd"-inspired masterpiece on this week's episode of "Disney's Magic Bake-Off"

Catch future cake creations every Friday at 8/7c, and watch past clips on @disneychannel and DisneyNOW!

Bunk’d Double Chocolate Chip Cake

INGREDIENTS:

2 c AP Flour
1 c cocoa powder
2 t baking powder
1 ½ t baking powder
¾ t cinnamon
½ t salt
2 c sugar
1 c brown sugar
6 eggs, room temp
½ c coffee
3t vanilla
1 ½ c sour cream
½ c vegetable oil
1 c mini chocolate chips, coat in flour

INSTRUCTIONS:

1. Preheat oven to 325°F

2. In a large bowl whisk together flour, cocoa powder, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon, brown sugar, granulated sugar, salt.

3. In a mixer add eggs, coffee, vegetable oil, vanilla extract and sour cream.

4. Add dry mix one cup at a time until well incorporated.
Coat chocolate chips with flour & fold into batter.

5. Prepare 2-6” pans and 2-8” with baking spray & parchment paper circles.

6. Bake cake for 20-30 mins or until a toothpick comes out clean.

7. Once cakes are cooled frost and enjoy.

FROSTING INGREDIENTS:

1 c unsalted butter
2 c powdered sugar
1T vanilla

INSTRUCTIONS:

1. In a clean mixer bowl cream butter and add vanilla until well blended.

2. Add powdered sugar in one cup at a time.

Ingredients:

1 cup heavy whipping cream
1/2 cup whole milk
1/2 cup granulated sugar
1 vanilla bean, seeded
4 large egg yolks
2 tablespoons cornstarch
Granulated or fine turbinado sugar, for bruleeing
1 pack waffle or sugar cones
1 (12-ounce) bag dark chocolate chips
1 (12-ounce) bag white chocolate chips
Sprinkles, for cone rim

Steps:

1. In a medium saucepan over low heat, combine the cream, milk, sugar and vanilla seeds. Heat until just simmering. Do not boil.

2. In a medium bowl, whisk together egg yolks and cornstarch.

3. Ladle a small amount of the warmed milk mixture into the egg yolks and whisk so no clumps form. Carefully add yolk mixture to warmed milk and whisk constantly for about 5 minutes.

4. Once the mixture is thick and slightly bubbling, remove from heat and pass through a fine-mesh sieve. Let the custard cool completely to room temperature.

5. Once the custard has cooled but not completely set, carefully pour into each chocolate-lined waffle cone. Refrigerate for 2 hours.

6. Just before serving, sprinkle granulated sugar on top of the custard and carefully use a torch to caramelize the sugar. The sugar will harden as it sits.

7. Crack the top with the back of a spoon and enjoy!

8. Using the microwave or double boiler, melt each chocolate in separate bowls.

9. Pour dark chocolate in each cone to coat the inside. Dip the rim of each cone in white chocolate and then in the sprinkles.

10. Let chocolate completely firm at room temperature or in the refrigerator.

Tiramisu Churros

Ingredients:

2 1/2 quarts vegetable oil
8 tablespoons unsalted butter, room temperature
2 tablespoons coffee liqueur
1 tablespoon Franjelico (hazelnut liqueur)
3 teaspoons granulated sugar
1 pinch	kosher salt
1 1/2 cups all-purpose flour
1/4 cup mascarpone
4 large eggs
For cocoa sugar:
1/2 cup granulated sugar
3 tablespoons hot cocoa mix
1 teaspoon dark unsweetened cocoa powder

Steps:

1. Heat the oil over medium heat to 365 degrees.

2. In a medium saucepan over medium heat, add the butter, coffee liqueur, Franjelico, sugar and salt until melted. Whisk to combine. Add the flour and using a wooden spoon, briskly stir the flour into the liquid until a dough forms. Continue to stir the dough for 1 to 2 minutes Turn off the heat and transfer the dough into the bowl of a stand mixer fitted with the paddle attachment. Mix the dough on low-medium speed and add the mascarpone. Mix to combine. Add 1 egg at a time, mixing until incorporated and increasing the speed with each addition until the dough is sticky and glossy. Pour the dough into a large (18-inch) piping bag fitted with a large star tip.

3. Pipe 3- to 4-inch churros into the hot oil, cutting the dough with scissors. Fry for 2 minutes until golden brown and then flip over to fry on the other side. You may need to manipulate them with a spider or slotted spoon in the hot oil so they fry evenly. Remove with a spider onto a paper towel-lined plate to drain of excess oil. Continue to fry in batches.

4. Put the cocoa sugar into a fine mesh sieve and dust the churros with sugar. (You can also roll the churros in the sugar, but dusting with sugar yields a more pleasant-looking sugar coating.)

5. Serve with the coffee custard.

Ingredients:

3 eggs, separated
3 tablespoons all-purpose flour
1 teaspoon salt
1 teaspoon baking soda
1 cup whole milk
1/2 cup butter, softened
1/2 cup sugar
1 teaspoon vanilla
2 cups blueberries
1 (12-ounce) container ricotta
2 tablespoons whole milk
Zest of 1 lemon
2 tablespoons lemon juice
1/2 teaspoon vanilla extract

Steps:

1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees, and spray the bottoms and sides of six 5-inch pie pans with nonstick spray.

2. In a medium bowl, whip the egg whites.

3. In another medium bowl, combine flour, salt and baking soda. Stir in the milk.

4. In a large bowl, cream together the butter, sugar and yolks.

5. Mix in flour mixture, then fold in the whites, followed by the vanilla.

6. Divide batter between the prepared tins.

7. Divide blueberries between the tins to cover the tops of the custards.

8. Bake for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

9. Add ricotta and milk to a bowl. Whip with a whisk until smooth.

10. Add lemon zest and juice and vanilla.

11. Spoon onto pies and serve warm.

On this week's "Disney's Magic Bake-Off," Kenady & Cayley used their decorating skills to whip up a cake full of enchantment. 

Catch future cake creations every Friday at 8/7c, and watch past clips on @disneychannel and DisneyNOW!

Coconut Pineapple Lime Cake

Ingredients:

1 c salted butter
2 c Sugar
6 eggs
1 T coconut emulsion
1 T Lime extract
3 t Baking Powder
2 t salt
2 t tart and sour flavoring
4 c AP flour
2  c whole milk
½ c fresh pineapple
½ c coconut shreds
2 c salted butter
4 c Powdered Sugar
2-3 T heavy cream
1 T coconut emulsion
1 T lime extract
1 t pineapple juice
½ juice of a lime
2 t salt
1 T ground ginger

Steps:

1. Preheat the oven to 350.

2. In a mixer cream butter and sugar.

3. Add eggs one at a time until well incorporated.

4. Add coconut emulsion and lime extract.

5. In a medium bowl, sift flour, baking powder and salt.

6. Alternate between milk and dry ingredients into creamed butter and sugar.

7. Fold in pineapple and coconut shreds.

8. Pour into 2- 6” pans and 2-8” pans and bake for 25- 30 mins.

9. Once cakes are completely cooled, frost and enjoy.

10. In a clean mixer bowl cream butter on high.

11. Add coconut emulsion, lime extract, pineapple juice, lime juice, salt, and ground ginger. Mix until well combined.

12. Add powdered sugar 1 cup at a time. If the frosting is too thick add heavy cream 1T at a time.

node.title: Flowers, pearls & a "glass" dome make this cake fit for a modern princess!

Ingredients:

For the espresso brownies:
4 eggs
1 1/2 cups sugar
1 teaspoon vanilla extract
1 cup butter, melted
2 tablespoons espresso powder
1/2 cup cocoa powder
1 cup all-purpose flour
1 teaspoon salt
1/2 teaspoon baking powder
3 (8-ounce) packages cream cheese, softened
1 1/2 cups sugar
1 teaspoon vanilla bean paste
3 large eggs, room temperature, divided
1/2 cup pumpkin puree
1/2 teaspoon pumpkin pie spice
In the prepared baking dish, pour the cream cheese mixture on top of the brownie batter and smooth to cover. Dollop 1-tablespoon portions of the pumpkin mixture in rows across the cream cheese. Use a knife or toothpick to create a swirl pattern, being careful not to go too deep to pull up any espresso brownie batter and without overworking the cream cheese topping.
Tent with foil, and bake for 40 to 45 minutes or until cheese is set. Cool to room temperature, and chill for at least 30 minutes before slicing.

Steps:

1. Preheat the oven to 350 degrees, and prepare a 9 by 13-inch baking dish with parchment paper and nonstick spray.

2. In a large mixing bowl, whisk eggs, sugar and vanilla. Slowly pour in the melted butter and whisk to combine. Fold in the espresso, cocoa powder, flour, salt and baking powder. Stir to combine but don’t over mix. Pour into the prepared baking dish and set aside.

3. In a large mixing bowl, beat the cream cheese and sugar until fluffy. Add vanilla and 2 eggs, and beat until incorporated. Set aside.

4. In a small mixing bowl, stir together pumpkin puree, pumpkin pie spice and the remaining egg.

The secret ingredient to these crispy chicken parmesan pillows? The perfect pot! We love our vintage-retro Dansk Casserole dish, and you will too: 
https://prf.hn/l/KMEV2MB

#promotion

Ingredients:

1 package crescent rolls
1 chicken breast, thinly sliced
1 tablespoon dried parsley
1 teaspoon dried thyme
1 teaspoon dried oregano
Salt
Pepper
Olive oil
8 ounces mozzarella cheese
Marinara sauce, for dipping
For the dredge:
2 cups Italian-style breadcrumbs
1 cup Parmesan cheese
3 eggs, beaten
3 cups all-purpose flour
Oil, for frying

Steps:

1. In a bowl, combine the chicken breast, dried parsley, dried thyme, dried oregano, salt, pepper and olive oil and toss to combine. Place chicken on a medium-high pan and cook on both sides until the internal temperature reaches 165 degrees. Once cooked, take chicken off the pan and allow to cool.

2. Using two pieces of the crescent dough, form a rectangle. Top one side of the dough with cheese and a piece of chicken. Add another layer of cheese over the chicken, and fold over the crescent dough so that it forms a pillow. Crimp the edges of the dough to properly seal closed.

3. In a small bowl, combine the breadcrumbs and the Parmesan cheese. Set up a dredging station with the beaten eggs, flour and breadcrumb mixture. Dredge each pillow by coating with flour first, then egg, and then the breadcrumb mixture. Shake off any excess breadcrumbs.

4. In a large heavy-bottomed stock pot or deep-fryer, heat vegetable oil to 350 degrees. Carefully add 1 or 2 pillows at a time and cook until golden brown. Remove and drain on a cooling rack.

5. Place all the pillows on a lined baking sheet, and put in a 350 degree oven for 10 minutes. Allow to cool slightly before serving. Serve alongside marinara sauce for dipping.

#ad Satisfy all your cheesy, creamy and crunchy cravings in one bite with rosemary bacon mac & cheese made with @lactaid Whole Milk & LACTAID Sour Cream — Made with 100% Real Milk, just without the lactose. 

Ingredients:

3 tbsp butter (contains low levels of lactose) or margarine
1 cup bread crumbs
1 cup grated parmesan (contains low levels of lactose)
1 tbsp rosemary, chopped
¼ cup parsley, chopped
5 pieces thick-cut bacon, chopped into ½ inch pieces
1 medium yellow onion, chopped
5 cloves garlic, chopped
2 tbsp fresh rosemary, chopped
1 tbsp unsalted butter (contains low levels of lactose) or margarine
3 tbsp all-purpose flour
2 cups Lactaid® Whole Milk
1 cup Lactaid® Sour Cream
1 tsp smoked paprika
1 ½ cups Swiss cheese, grated (contains low levels of lactose)
2 ½ cups sharp cheddar cheese, shredded (contains low levels of lactose)
1 tbsp kosher salt
1 tsp freshly ground black pepper
1 tsp red pepper flakes
16 oz elbow macaroni, cooked slightly al dente

Steps:

1. In a small non-stick skillet make the topping: Heat the butter or margarine over medium heat. Add the rosemary and breadcrumbs and stir to toast. Add the parmesan cheese and parsley and remove from heat.

2. Preheat oven to 350°.

3. In a stock pot, over medium high heat, cook the bacon until fat has rendered and bacon is crispy. Remove the bacon.

4. To the stock pot add the onion and garlic. Cook until the onions are softened.

5. While the vegetables are cooking, pour the Lactaid® Whole Milk into a saucepan and warm over low heat. Once simmering, add the rosemary and stir.

6. Add the butter or margarine and flour to the stockpot with the onions and garlic and cook until the flour is browned. Add in the warmed rosemary milk mixture.

7. Once the mixture comes to a light simmer and has begun to thicken. Remove from heat and add the paprika, cheese, salt, red pepper flakes, reserved bacon and sour cream. Stir to combine.

8. In a large mixing bowl combine cheese sauce with cooked macaroni and mix thoroughly. Pour into a greased 9x13 pan.

9. Evenly distribute the breadcrumb topping over the top of the mac and cheese.

10. Bake for 15-20 mins or until the topping is golden brown.

This is your excuse to have dessert before 10 a.m.

Ingredients:

1 cup Water
1 cup White Sugar
2/3 cup Cocoa Powder
1 tsp Vanilla extract
2 shots Espresso
1 cup Whole Milk
Ice cubes
3 oz Dark Chocolate
Chocolate syrup
Chocolate chips
Whipped cream
Chocolate cake slice/Chocolate chip cookie

Steps:

1. Combine water, white sugar and cocoa powder in a saucepan over

2. low heat.

3. Whisk constantly until the sugar dissolves and the mixture thickens.

4. Remove from the heat and add vanilla extract. Chill for 1 hour.

5. Melt the dark chocolate. Take a drinking glass/jar and dip it in the

6. melted chocolate and then again in the chocolate chips.

7. Squirt chocolate sauce over the internal sides of the glass and pour

8. some extra at the bottom.

9. Add the ice and pour the espresso shots. Then pour the milk.

10. Top the drinking glass/jar with whipped cream and garnish with a

11. straw and a chocolate chip cookie/chocolate cake slice.

Ingredients:

1/2 cup milk
1/2 cup water
1 cup all-purpose flour
2 eggs
1/4 teaspoon salt
2 tablespoons butter, melted
1 tablespoon olive oil
3 cloves garlic, minced
3 cups fresh spinach
2 cups chicken breast, cooked and shredded
1 cup mozzarella cheese, shredded
Juice of a lemon
Salt and pepper
2 tablespoons butter
2 tablespoons flour
1 1/4 cups milk, warm
Salt
Freshly ground pepper
1/8 teaspoon nutmeg

Steps:

1. Preheat oven to 375 degrees.

2. In a blender, add milk, water, flour, eggs, salt and melted butter. Blend until smooth. Refrigerate for at least 30 minutes.

3. Lightly oil a frying pan with melted butter. Place over medium-high heat.

4. Pour in 1/4 cup batter, and tilt the pan with a circular motion until the batter coats the surface evenly.

5. Cook the crepe for about 2 minutes, until it bubbles up and loosens from the pan. Flip and cook for 2 more minutes on the other side.

6. In a heavy-bottomed pan on medium-high heat, add 1 tablespoon of olive oil.

7. Add garlic and cook until aromatic, about 2 minutes.

8. Add spinach, chicken and mozzarella and cook for 4 minutes.

9. Add lemon juice and season with salt and pepper.

10. Place crepe on a baking sheet or cast-iron pan, place 2 tablespoons of filling in the center and fold up. Repeat with remaining crepes.

11. Pour sauce over the crepes, and broil for 5 to 8 minutes until golden brown.

12. In a heavy-bottomed saucepan, melt butter.

13. Stir in the flour and cook, stirring constantly, until it cooks out, about 2 minutes.

14. Add the warm milk, salt, pepper, and nutmeg, continuing to stir as the sauce thickens.

15. Bring to a boil, then remove from heat.

node.text:
Swap your chicken for cauliflower, never look back.

Ingredients:

1 head cauliflower, cut into large florets
1 tablespoon cornstarch
1 teaspoon baking soda
Salt, to taste
3/4 cup water
1 cup rice flour
Vegetable oil, for frying
1/4 cup vegetable stock
3 tablespoons soy sauce
2 tablespoons rice wine vinegar
2 tablespoons Chinese cooking wine
2 teaspoons sesame oil
3 tablespoons sugar
1 tablespoon cornstarch
1 tablespoon water
5 dried red chilies
Toasted sesame seeds, for garnish
Thinly sliced scallions, for garnish

Steps:

1. In a large bowl, mix together the cornstarch, baking soda, salt, water and rice flour until it forms a batter.

2. Toss in the cauliflower and fold together until well coated.

3. In a large heavy-bottomed pot, heat the oil to 375 degrees.

4. Fry the cauliflower in batches until golden brown, about 3 minutes.

5. Transfer to a plate lined with paper towels to drain.

6. Add all of the sauce ingredients except the chilies.

7. Whisk together until everything is combined.

8. Bring to a boil and whisk occasionally until sauce thickens, about 2 minutes.

9. Add the dried chilies and simmer for 2 more minutes. Remove from heat.

10. Add the cauliflower to the sauce and toss to coat. Sprinkle with thinly sliced scallions and sesame seeds as garnish.

Classic pirouette wafers just got a supersized upgrade.

Ingredients:

14 oz dark chocolate chips
1 3/4 cups heavy cream
1/2 cup icing sugar
1/3 cup butter, melted
1 tbsp heavy cream
1/2 tsp vanilla
2 egg whites
Pinch salt
1/2 cup flour
1 tsp cocoa powder

Steps:

1. Warm the cream, and pour over the chocolate chips.

2. Let stand for 1 minute, then slowly whisk together.

3. Chill for 30 minutes.

4. Use an electric whisk to whip until light and fluffy.

5. Pour out onto plastic wrap and form into a sausage, the same length as your pan.

6. Put in the fridge for 2 hours.

7. Preheat the oven to 375 degrees.

8. Line a Swiss roll pan with baking paper.

9. In a large bowl, mix together the icing sugar, melted butter, heavy cream and vanilla.

10. Using an electric hand whisk, mix in the egg whites until the mixture is light and fluffy. Add the flour and salt and fold through until just mixed.

11. Put three tablespoons of the mixture into a separate bowl and stir in the cocoa powder.

12. Transfer to a piping bag and cut a small hole in the end.

13. Spread the plain mixture across the baking sheet, then pipe diagonal chocolate lines across the whole sheet. Just before you put it in the oven, unwrap the ganache sausage, and trim the ends flat.

14. Bake the wafer for 5 to 6 minutes. Watch it carefully and take it out of the oven when the edges are brown and the top is just starting to color.

15. Flip the wafer out onto a clean work surface.

16. Start to roll the long edge nearest you around a rolling pin to create the start of the round shape, then swap the rolling pin for the ganache sausage and roll up like a cigar.

17. Allow it to set for 5 minutes, seam side down, before slicing and serving.
